title: Menkauhor Kaiu
summary: Menkauhor Kaiu (also known as Ikauhor and in Greek as Mencherês, Μεγχερῆς)[16] was an Ancient Egyptian pharaoh of the Old Kingdom period. He was the seventh ruler of the Fifth Dynasty at the end of the 25th century BC or early in the 24th century BC ( circa 2399–2390 BC ).
